    "content1": "<p>Lingual Orthodontics, popularly known as invisible braces, internal braces or hidden braces, is a technique where the demand is increasing day by day, and the lingual orthodontic treatment is a technique in which brackets and braces are used to correct the irregularities in the teeth, instead of the front surfaces of the teeth on the side of the lips. The most important advantage of this technique is that it is not visible at all. Today, there are custom-made lingual appliances available. Thanks to its personal structure, unlike other lingual treatment methods, the treatment results are very successful.</p>",
    "accord1title": "Is every case suitable for lingual orthodontics?",
